b'' b'the otis project presents...' b'' b'synergy: revolt' b'...the first in a continuing series of collaborative' b'art initiatives designed to exploit the binarity' b'of the infosphere. this series of diversely' b'structured art-manipulation projects will attempt' b'to stretch across network boundries encouraging' b'use of electronic mail, fax, video, photography,' b'scanned "conventional" art and even sound to' b'create multi-artist "still" visuals in gif and' b'jpg formats. visualists from all technical levels' b'are welcome.' b'' b'revolt will be structured simply. there will be' b'three stages of production. the first stage will' b'consist of all participants creating one still' b'work as a "starter" piece that two other partici-' b'pants will, in turn, manipulate. all first stage' b'"base" images are due by sunday, may 23rd, b'midnight central daylight time.' b'' b'stage two will begin on may 24th. all images will' b'be sent to another (arbitrarily chosen) participant' b'for them to do manipulations on in anyway they see' b'fit. for purely digital artists, this may consist' b'of filtering the image through their favorite paint' b'program. for "analog" artists, this may well be' b'printing a hardcopy of the image and adding their' b'own part with pen, pencil or white-out then scan-' b'ning in the image again to be transferred on to' b'the third-stage artist. all second-stage works' b'are due by midnight on sunday, may 30th.' b'' b'stage three is the finishing stage and will begin' b'on may 31st. all artists will do what they think' b"it takes to finish up the image they've been given" b'using whatever technique they see as worthy.' b'these images will be due on june 6th, midnight.' b'' b'all involved will participate in each stage of' b'creation.' b'' b'-----------------------------------------------------------' b'to join, send email/mail with the following info:' b'' b'name:' b'email address:' b'mail address:' b'scanner access? (color/grey/none)' b'printer access? (laser/postscript/inkjet/color/dot)' b'computer access? (mac/ibm-pc/sun/amiga/atari/next/other)' b'output format?\t (tiff/targa/gif/jpeg/pict/postscript/fax' b'/photocopy/pcx/windows bitmap)' b'graphics level? (8bit/16bit/24bit/?)' b'ftp access?' b'time limitations?' b'' b'address the information to:' b'' b'(include "revolt" in the subject line)' b'mail: the otis project' b'synergy: revolt' b'po bx b'omaha, ne b'' b'---------------------------------------------------------' b'remember, all starter images are due on sunday, may 23rd.' b'deposit them at either of these ftp sites:' b'' b'sunsite.unc.edu (/pub/multimedia/pictures/otis/incoming)' b'or' b'141.214.4.135 (projects/otis/incoming)' b'or' b'...send uuencoded images to us via email...' b'or' b'...send hardcopies to address above...' b'or' b'...arrange fax exchange.' b'' b"if you don't get your starter image in, you won't be" b'able to participate until synergy phase ii (in mid-june).' b'---------------------------------------------------------' b'' b'we will do our best to accomodate/facilitate image exchange' b'for the "technologically impaired". if you don\'t have' b"access to a scanner, but need one, we'll try to help." b'if you need an image printed out and sent to you, let' b'us know (send an sase if you anticipate this).' b'' b'additional information available on the following:' b'- suggestions for use of "uncommon" mediums' b'(such as video stills, electronic imaging and sound)' b'- fax availability times' b'- "copyright" considerations (appropriation)' b'- image conversion' b'- the otis project in general' b'' b'--' b'andy booth were you ever abducted by aliens? ever see elvis' b'po bx at the local i would like to hear from you' b'omaha, ne about any paranormal experiences you have had.' 